04/06/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The foreign ministers of Russia and the 28 NATO member-states will meet on June 27th on the Greek island of Corfu, NATO Spokesman James Appathurai announced on Wednesday (June 3rd). The meeting of the NATO-Russia Council was supposed to take place on May 20th in Brussels. Russia cancelled it to protest NATO's military exercises in Georgia and the expulsion of two diplomats from the Russian delegation in NATO. (AFP, RIA-Novosti, DPA, AP - 03/06/09)
